                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/1556: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-06-15T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1923—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. I informed President Borno that it would be useless to proceed with drafting
                    of internal revenue laws unless the question of control was definitely settled
                    and that in my opinion such control must be placed absolutely in American hands.
                    President Borno informed me that he was of the same opinion.</p>
                <p>I thereupon stated that I would shortly have a project to present to him.</p>
                <p>Believe an agreement should be made cover this question and one or two others in
                    connection therewith. I will shortly be able to submit the general terms
                    proposed to the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
